<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Compound Interest Problem</h2>
    <p>Question: A sum of ₹4000 amounts to ₹4840 in 2 years at compound interest. Find the rate of interest.</p>

    <div class="step">
      Formula: <span class="highlight">A = P (1 + R/100)<sup>T</sup></span>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      Substitute values: 
      <div>
        <span class="numberBox">4840</span> = 
        <span class="numberBox">4000</span> (1 + R/100)<sup>2</sup>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      Divide both sides: 
      <div>
        <span class="fraction">
          <span class="top">4840</span>
          <span class="bottom">4000</span>
        </span>
        = (1 + R/100)<sup>2</sup>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      Simplify: <span class="numberBox">1.21</span> = (1 + R/100)<sup>2</sup>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      Square root: <span class="numberBox">1.1</span> = 1 + R/100
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      Subtract 1: R/100 = <span class="numberBox">0.1</span>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      Multiply: R = <span class="highlight">10%</span>
    </div>
  </div>
